CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 28, 1956, pg. A24, reads: "Aid YM-YWCA Fund Drive - The Merry Accents, Y-Teen Club, sponsored a bake sale at Peabody High School, Tuesday afternoon, with part of the proceeds going to the current YM-YWCA Building Fund Campaign. Attractive salesgirls are, left to right, Aubrey Coddington, Carol Brown, 'Ginny' Kerr, president, and Louise Capozzi, adviser. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Aubrey Coddington, Carol Brown, 'Ginny' Kerr, and Louise Capozzi standing behind table handing items to women and girls during YMCA and YWCA bake sale fund drive in Peabody High School
